Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.61,0:22:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mai-chan, do you know what Joseki is?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.32,0:22:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.82,0:22:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseki is a set pattern of moves, researched\Nby people over a long period of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.76,0:22:18.01,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(209,0)\3c&H058B0B&\4c&H058B0B&\fscx99\fscy90\bord1\shad0.5\move(780,356,313,356)}Joseki... born from studying Go since long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.01,0:22:21.67,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(0,42)\3c&H058B0B&\4c&H058B0B&\fscx99\fscy90\bord1\shad0.5\pos(313,356)}Joseki... born from studying Go since long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.67,0:22:24.94,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs22\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(42,501)\3c&H058B0B&\4c&H058B0B&\fscx98\fscy100\bord1\shad0.5\pos(313,356)}Joseki... set pattern of play that leads to equal results.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.79,0:22:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the lead to equal benefits for both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.10,0:22:41.69,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs22\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(0,542)\3c&HD500CC&\4c&HD500CC&\fscx98\fscy100\bord1\shad0.5\pos(164,47)}~Example of a Joseki~
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.10,0:22:27.42,Background,,0,0,0,,Let me introduce a common one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.54,0:22:31.24,Background,,0,0,0,,White goes to Keima to attack Black's Hoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.33,0:22:33.04,Background,,0,0,0,,and Black responds with another Keima.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.04,0:22:35.66,Background,,0,0,0,,White does a Suberi to reduce Black's territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.66,0:22:38.83,Background,,0,0,0,,and Black stops White with a Kosumi to\Nprevent White from going any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.83,0:22:42.84,Background,,0,0,0,,And to stabilize his shape, White\Ndoes a two space jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.24,0:22:44.49,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs22.5\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(375,0)\3c&H0000F3&\4c&H0000F3&\fscx100\fscy100\bord1\shad0.5\pos(163,43)}Both sides have an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.24,0:22:44.49,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs21\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(375,0)\3c&H0000F3&\4c&H0000F3&\fscx99\fscy105\bord1\shad0.5\pos(256,97)}equal amount of territory
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.83,0:22:44.49,Background,,0,0,0,,This is Joseki.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.49,0:22:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the shortest Joseki there is, and it\Nis commonly used even in pro games.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.13,0:22:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the only Joseki?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.20,0:22:55.67,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs22\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(0,375)\3c&H058B0B&\4c&H058B0B&\fscx99\fscy100\bord1\shad0.5\pos(272,273)}There are lots of other Joseki{\i1}!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.20,0:22:55.67,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs24\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(0,375)\3c&H058B0B&\4c&H058B0B&\fscx99\fscy90\bord1\shad0.5\pos(351,354)}Learn the important ones as you get better{\i1}!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.50,0:22:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There are tons of others,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.42,0:22:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but you only need to remember\Na few important ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.08,0:22:56.15,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs29\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(83,0)\3c&H1300EF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\fscx99\fscy100\bord2\shad1\move(305,265,305,306)}To be continued...
